HEADWORD: localized
<hw>localized</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Medicine)</fld>
<def>confined or restricted to a particular location; <as>as, the
<ex>localized</ex> infection formed a definite abscess</as>. Contrasted
with <contr>disseminated</contr> or <contr>systemic</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>made local or oriented locally; <as>as, a
decentralized and <ex>localized</ex> political authority</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Locally</ent>⟦br⟧
